TY  - JOUR
TI  - Aggregation of Variables in Dynamic Systems
AU  - Simon, Herbert A.
AU  - Ando, Albert
AB  - [Previous studies have examined dynamic systems that are decomposable into independent subsystems. This article treats of systems that are nearly decomposable--systems with matrices whose elements, except within certain submatrices along the main diagonal, approach zero in the limit. Such a system can be represented as a superposition of (1) a set of independent subsystems (one for each submatrix on the diagonal) and (2) an aggregate system having one variable for each subsystem. This superposition separates short-run from long-run dynamics and justifies the ignoring of "weak" linkages in partial equilibrium studies.]
C1  - Full publication date: Apr., 1961
DB  - JSTOR
DO  - 10.2307/1909285
EP  - 138
IS  - 2
PB  - [Wiley, Econometric Society]
PY  - 1961
SN  - 00129682, 14680262
SP  - 111
T2  - Econometrica
