TY  - JOUR
TI  - Nonlinear Programming by the Simplex Method
AU  - Hartley, H. O.
AB  - [Nonlinear programming is a numerical technique of computing the "optimum levels" of "activities" for an organization or enterpreneur wishing to maximize an "objective function" (say, profit). While with "linear programming" profit is a "linear function" of the activity levels which are linearly constrained, the present methods permit nonlinear functional relationships of a particular type.]
